{"id":25915,"date":"2018-02-07T13:31:58","date_gmt":"2018-02-07T09:31:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25915"},"modified":"2019-08-05T12:05:31","modified_gmt":"2019-08-05T08:05:31","slug":"question-wish-not-asked","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/02\/07\/question-wish-not-asked\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Miracles: Question the Prophet wished he had not asked"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>I asked my Lord a question I wish I had not asked. I said: O Lord, there were messengers before me, among them those for whom you subordinated the wind and among them those who resurrected the dead. Allah said: Did I not find you as an orphan and give you refuge? Did I not find you lost and guided you? Have I not opened your heart and lifted your burdens? I said: Of course, O Lord.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Awsat\u0323 3776<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p>Ibn Hazm said, &#8220;If there were no other miracle besides the biography of the Prophet (s\u0323), it would be enough.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Fi\u1e63al fil-Milal 2\/73<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e <strong>\u0633\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0631\u064e\u0628\u0651\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0629\u064b \u0648\u064e\u062f\u0650\u062f\u0652\u062a\u064